{% comment %}
  Practitioner Auto-Apply — HEADLESS APP EMBED (renders no visible UI).

  For a logged-in patient already attributed to a practitioner, this auto-applies
  their currently-assigned practitioner code to the cart session using Shopify's
  NATIVE /discount/<code> endpoint — so the discount lands as a normal applied
  discount and carries into checkout, with the buyer typing nothing and NO block
  placed on any page.

  APP EMBED (target: "body"): enabled once under Theme editor → App embeds →
  "Practitioner Auto-Apply". It is NOT a section block — the merchant never drops
  it on the Cart template. It renders site-wide but only ACTS once the cart has
  items (so browsing with an empty cart never triggers a redirect).

  Source of the code: the customer's `code:<code>` Shopify tag, which
  syncCustomerCodeTag keeps to exactly ONE entry = the LATEST code the
  practitioner assigned (portal "Assign discount code"). Read here in Liquid —
  no backend round-trip.

  Re-applies on every cart refresh: if the assigned code is NOT currently on the
  cart — because the buyer REMOVED it, or they went straight to the cart without
  it ever being applied — it is (re)applied. If a DIFFERENT/stale code is on the
  cart (e.g. left over after the practitioner reassigned/revoked), it's cleared
  and the assigned one applied. So "buyer removes the code → refresh → it comes
  back" works, and a reassignment takes effect on an existing cart.

  Loop-safe: "present on the cart" is judged regardless of `applicable`, so once
  the code is on the cart we stop (no reload loop even if a Function ORDER
  discount computes $0 or isn't fully surfaced in /cart.json). A per-code attempt
  budget (sessionStorage `cdo_apply_n:<code>`, cap MAX) is RESET to 0 whenever the
  code is confirmed present — so a later manual removal always gets a fresh
  budget to re-apply — and only caps a code that can NEVER land, bounding a
  worst-case loop to MAX reloads instead of forever.

  STALE detection uses REAL entered codes only (cart.discount_codes[].code) —
  NOT cart_level_discount_applications titles. This Function-backed discount's
  application title is its ADMIN title ("Practitioner code — <code>"), not the
  bare code; counting it as a "stale foreign code" meant the correct-state
  branch never fired, the budget never reset, and MAX was exhausted so a removed
  code never came back. Application titles are used only to CONFIRM the assigned
  code is applied, never to flag a stale one.

  NOTE 1 — CHECKOUT: this is an Online Store app embed, so it runs on the cart
  (and other storefront pages), NOT on the checkout pages. On Shopify Grow,
  checkout UI extensions on the core checkout steps are Plus-only, so a code
  removed INSIDE checkout cannot be re-applied there by an extension; the code
  applied at the cart carries into checkout automatically. (On Plus, the
  checkout-ui-code extension can be re-enabled to cover checkout.)
  NOTE 2 — REVOKED: this only renders when the customer still has a code:<code>
  tag. A fully-revoked patient (no tag) isn't force-cleared here — the checkout
  Function declines a stale code regardless, so it can't discount the order.
{% endcomment %}

{%- assign cdo_code = '' -%}
{%- if customer -%}
  {%- for tag in customer.tags -%}
    {%- assign tag_down = tag | downcase -%}
    {%- if tag_down contains 'code:' -%}
      {%- assign cdo_code = tag | split: ':' | last | strip -%}
    {%- endif -%}
  {%- endfor -%}
{%- endif -%}

{%- if cdo_code != '' -%}
<script>
(function () {
  var code = {{ cdo_code | json }};
  if (!code) return;
  var lower = String(code).toLowerCase();
  // Attempt budget per code per tab session. It is RESET to 0 every time the
  // code is confirmed present on the cart, so a later manual removal always
  // gets a fresh budget to re-apply on the next refresh. The cap only bites
  // when a code can NEVER land (declined / not surfaced) — bounding a runaway
  // reload loop to MAX attempts instead of looping forever.
  var countKey = 'cdo_apply_n:' + lower;
  var MAX = 6;

  fetch('/cart.json', { headers: { Accept: 'application/json' }, credentials: 'include' })
    .then(function (r) { return r.ok ? r.json() : null; })
    .then(function (cart) {
      if (!cart) return;

      // Only act once there's something to discount. If the cart is empty we
      // return WITHOUT touching the budget, so it re-checks on the next
      // navigation and applies as soon as the buyer adds an item — covering
      // cart-drawer themes with no visit to the /cart page.
      var itemCount = typeof cart.item_count === 'number' ? cart.item_count : 0;
      if (itemCount <= 0) return;

      // REAL, removable discount codes entered on the cart. Each entry in
      // `discount_codes` carries a `.code` — the only thing a shopper can
      // actually type into (or remove from) the native discount field. This
      // drives BOTH "is the assigned code present" and "is a stale/foreign code
      // present". NOTE: presence is judged regardless of `applicable` — a code
      // that's on the cart (even if the Function currently gives it $0) is still
      // "present", and re-adding it wouldn't change that. Presence is what lets
      // us re-apply after a removal WITHOUT looping: once it's on the cart we
      // stop.
      var codes = (Array.isArray(cart.discount_codes) ? cart.discount_codes : [])
        .map(function (dc) { return String((dc && dc.code) || '').toLowerCase(); })
        .filter(Boolean);

      // Order-level discount APPLICATIONS. For this Function-backed code
      // discount the application `title` is the discount's ADMIN title
      // ("Practitioner code — <code>"), NOT the bare code — so it must NEVER be
      // treated as a foreign/stale code: you can't remove an application by
      // title, and doing so mistook the assigned discount's OWN application for
      // a stale code, which meant the "correct state" branch never fired, the
      // attempt budget was never reset, and it burned through MAX so a later
      // manual removal never re-applied ("removed code doesn't come back").
      // Used ONLY as a secondary confirmation the assigned code is applied.
      var appTitles = (Array.isArray(cart.cart_level_discount_applications)
        ? cart.cart_level_discount_applications : [])
        .map(function (a) { return String((a && (a.code || a.title)) || '').toLowerCase(); })
        .filter(Boolean);

      var assignedPresent =
        codes.indexOf(lower) !== -1 ||
        appTitles.some(function (t) { return t === lower || t.indexOf(lower) !== -1; });
      // Any REAL code on the cart that is NOT the patient's currently-assigned
      // one — e.g. left over after the practitioner reassigned/revoked it. The
      // practitioner discount is non-combinable, so a stale one must be cleared.
      // Derived from real codes only, so the assigned discount's own application
      // title is never mistaken for a stale code.
      var stale = codes.filter(function (c) { return c !== lower; });

      // Correct state: the assigned code is on the cart and nothing stale is.
      // Reset the attempt budget so a future removal re-applies from scratch.
      if (assignedPresent && stale.length === 0) {
        try { sessionStorage.removeItem(countKey); } catch (e) {}
        return;
      }

      // Otherwise (re)apply: the assigned code is missing (removed by the buyer,
      // or never applied — e.g. straight-to-cart), or a stale code is present.
      // This is what makes "buyer removes the code → refresh → it comes back"
      // work. Bounded by MAX so a code that can't land can't reload forever.
      var n = 0;
      try { n = parseInt(sessionStorage.getItem(countKey) || '0', 10) || 0; } catch (e) {}
      if (n >= MAX) return;
      try { sessionStorage.setItem(countKey, String(n + 1)); } catch (e) {}

      var back = window.location.pathname + window.location.search;
      var go = function () {
        window.location.href =
          '/discount/' + encodeURIComponent(code) +
          '?redirect=' + encodeURIComponent(back);
      };
      // Clear any existing (stale / non-combinable) code first so the assigned
      // code takes effect, then apply. Best-effort — go regardless (applying a
      // non-combinable order discount also replaces a stale one on its own).
      fetch('/cart/update.js', {
        method: 'POST',
        headers: { 'Content-Type': 'application/json' },
        body: JSON.stringify({ discount: '' }),
      }).then(go, go);
    })
    .catch(function () {});
})();
</script>
{%- endif -%}

{% schema %}
{
  "name": "Practitioner Auto-Apply",
  "target": "body",
  "settings": []
}
{% endschema %}
